<!-- STRATEGIC INSIGHTS -->
<section class="insights-section">
  <h2 style="color: white; border-bottom-color: #aa8a34; margin-top: 0;">8 Strategic Insights - Pricing Mastery</h2>
  
  <div class="insights-grid">
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">1</div>
      <div class="insight-title">Segmentation First</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Orice pricing strategy care nu e bazatƒÉ pe segmentare e guess work. Noi am identificat 3 segmente clare, fiecare cu different willingness to pay »ôi use cases.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">2</div>
      <div class="insight-title">Value > Cost</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Pricing based pe cost e suboptimal. Value-based pricing (ce value deliver) maximizeaza revenue. Enterprise segments pagesc 10x mai mult pentru feature set similar.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">3</div>
      <div class="insight-title">3 Tiers Optimal</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Am testat 2, 3, 4 tiers. 3 tiers e sweet spot: enough differentiation, nu overwhelm buyers. 4 tiers complexity outweighs benefits.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">4</div>
      <div class="insight-title">Feature Bundling Keys</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Nu e care features e mai scump. E care bundles de features create maximum perceived value difference. Enterprise e Enterprise + priority support + custom integrations.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">5</div>
      <div class="insight-title">Anchoring Effect Powerful</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Highest price tier e anchor. Enterprise la 999 EUR/mo makes Professional la 349 EUR/mo look like "good deal". Psychological pricing FTW.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">6</div>
      <div class="insight-title">Migration Gradual Better</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Existing customers keep old pricing, new ones get new pricing. Reduce friction, increase acceptance. Churn stay low, new revenue compounds.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">7</div>
      <div class="insight-title">ARPU > Customer Count</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Growing ARPU 42% beats growing customer count 50%. Lower CAC on high-value segments, higher LTV = better unit economics.</div>
    </div>
    
    <div class="insight-card">
      <div class="insight-number">8</div>
      <div class="insight-title">Churn Reduction = Revenue</div>
      <div class="insight-text">Optimizing pricing reduced churn 40%. Existing customers happier, retention improved. Churn reduction = direct revenue lift.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

