<!-- LESSONS LEARNED -->
<section class="lessons-section">
  <h2 style="color: #1a1a1a; margin-top: 0;">Lessons Learned & Framework Transfer</h2>
  
  <div class="lesson-item">
    <div class="lesson-title">1. Pricing E Strategic, Nu Operational</div>
    <div class="lesson-text">Pricing decisions impact revenue, margin, unit economics, customer perception. Trebuie handled la strategic level, nu operational. Board-level discussion + data-driven framework.</div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="lesson-item">
    <div class="lesson-title">2. Segmentation E Foundation</div>
    <div class="lesson-text">Nu putem optimiza pricing fƒÉrƒÉ clarity pe segmente. Diferite segmente = diferite WTP, use cases, decision processes. One-size-fits-all pricing e suboptimal.</div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="lesson-item">
    <div class="lesson-title">3. Gradual Migration Reduce Risk</div>
    <div class="lesson-text">Big bang pricing changes = customer churn. Gradual migration (existing customers keep old pricing) = low friction, higher adoption. Patience = higher net revenue.</div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="lesson-item">
    <div class="lesson-title">4. Data + Psychology = Optimal Pricing</div>
    <div class="lesson-text">Use data (WTP surveys, analytics) + psychology (anchoring, bundling, FOMO) to design pricing. Balance scientific + behavioral approaches.</div>
  </div>
</section>

